1
00:00:06,680 --> 00:00:09,120
MORAN: Private journal
of Captain Jonathan Moran.

2
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:11,720
21st November, 211789.

3
00:00:11,840 --> 00:00:15,560
We have located a craft
of unknown origin on the lake floor.

4
00:00:15,640 --> 00:00:18,000
Visual scans in situ revealed nothing.

5
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:21,000
So, we have brought the craft on-board

6
00:00:21,080 --> 00:00:23,800
and myself and the crew
will now investigate.

7
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:32,880
MORAN: How did they miss this
in the initial survey?

8
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:36,400
Cass says it was buried.

9
00:00:36,840 --> 00:00:40,760
And the currents of the water
must have shifted the rubble around.

10
00:00:40,840 --> 00:00:43,520
Conversation needs to be had
about who owns this spaceship.

11
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:45,320
MORAN: Can we stop
calling it a spaceship?

12
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,000
We don't know what it is.

13
00:00:47,080 --> 00:00:49,480
PRITCHARD: A case could be made
that this is an asset

14
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:51,600
and my company has bought
the rights to all assets...

15
00:00:51,680 --> 00:00:52,680
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

16
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:54,960
What's this?

17
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:57,640
Lunn, grab me a torch, will you?

18
00:00:57,880 --> 00:01:02,440
It was found on MOD property,
even if that property is underwater.

19
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:09,880
MORAN: Lunn, where's the torch?

20
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:29,640
CanIgo in?

21
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:32,080
What is the, uh, radiation count?

22
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:33,800
PRITCHARD: Pretty much background level.

23
00:01:33,880 --> 00:01:36,600
Anything more it would have shown up
in the initial survey 20 years ago.

24
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:38,840
If it's not safe,
how come you can go in?

25
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:42,720
How long do you think
it's been down here?

26
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:44,960
Well, there's next to no corrosion.

27
00:01:45,320 --> 00:01:48,640
-I've not seen technology like this...
-Please, don't say "On Earth".

28
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:50,880
-...on Earth before.
-(SIGHS) Oh.

29
00:01:50,960 --> 00:01:52,120
-(CHUCKLES)
-Maybe it's some kind

30
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:53,320
of experimental craft

31
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:55,520
that got left behind
when they abandoned the site.

32
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:58,320
Wait, you think the army
would just lose a prototype weapon?

33
00:01:58,880 --> 00:02:01,080
You're new to the military
aren't you, son?

34
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,480
BENNETT: Cass says he might be right.

35
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:06,760
It might have been here since the 1980s,
before the valley flooded.

36
00:02:09,920 --> 00:02:11,040
Cass!

37
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:13,520
(BEEPING)

38
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:15,800
(SCREAMS)

39
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:17,280
LUNN: Come on!

40
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:20,240
-Move!
-LUNN: Come on! We have to go now!

41
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:25,640
TANNOY: Fire in main hangar.

42
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:28,840
Safety protocols have been initiated.

43
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:31,120
All crew must evacuate immediately.

44
00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:34,440
This safety message was
brought to you by Vector Petroleum.

45
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:36,080
We can't just leave him in there!

46
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:37,760
There's something in the spaceship.
I saw it!

47
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:39,920
O'Donnell. O'Donnell, he's dead.
Didn't you see him?

48
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,480
Are we... The fire,
are we safe out here?

49
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:43,040
It's fine,
the CO2 will put the fire out.

50
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:44,280
It was you!

51
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:46,480
You were messing about
with the controls on that ship!

52
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:48,960
(SCREAMS)

53
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:53,840
Moran.

54
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:56,080
We just saw you...

55
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:59,280
He's... Oh, my God.

56
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:02,920
He's a ghost.

57
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:07,800
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

58
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:53,640
(WHOOSHING)

59
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:03,480
What's wrong? You're not happy.

60
00:04:04,880 --> 00:04:06,760
Why aren't you happy? Tell me.

61
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:09,040
CLARA: Come on, we're on a roll!

62
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:11,440
Monsters, things blowing up.

63
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,360
Oh, hey, can we go back to that place

64
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:14,600
where the people
with the long necks have been

65
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:16,240
celebrating New Year for two centuries?

66
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,760
I left my sunglasses there.

67
00:04:18,840 --> 00:04:20,920
And most of my dignity.

68
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:22,920
DOCTOR: Why have you brought us here?

69
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:26,440
(EXHALES) Here, being?

70
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:31,520
Underwater.

71
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,760
Some sort of a base.

72
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:37,120
Technology's 22nd century.

73
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:39,840
Maybe military. Maybe scientific.

74
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,360
Is there a crew?

75
00:04:42,080 --> 00:04:44,280
Must be. Somewhere. There's oxygen.

76
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,520
(SIGHING) I want another adventure.

77
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,720
Come on, you feel the same.

78
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:54,840
You're itching to save
a planet, I know it.

79
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:03,960
Doctor, look at this.

80
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:07,640
Well, looks like you got your wish.

81
00:05:08,840 --> 00:05:09,840
CLARA: Food fight?

82
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:11,480
DOCTOR: I think there was
more to it than that.

83
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:13,600
Whatever it was,
it happened pretty recently.

84
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,840
Seven or eight hours ago.

85
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:20,320
No bodies, though.

86
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:23,520
And they took provisions.

87
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:28,840
OK, so, something or someone
forced the crew to abandon the base.

88
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:32,080
Maybe they went for a swim
in the creepy,

89
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:33,600
flooded village outside.

90
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:36,640
Oh, yeah, you see, this is more like it.

91
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:42,480
Well, come on. Don't leave me hanging.

92
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,360
Look, told you.

93
00:05:58,320 --> 00:05:59,320
Crew.

94
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:03,040
Hello, sailors.

95
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:16,360
Right, did not expect that.

96
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:17,960
Hands up, who expected that.

97
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:22,400
Wait, wait, wait.
I don't think they're going to hurt us.

98
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:24,200
I think that they're just curious.

99
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,000
You sure?

100
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:30,840
Well, I mean, define "sure".

101
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:35,080
Look at you, lovely chaps.

102
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:36,920
What's happened to you, then?

103
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:45,440
Come on.

104
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:50,200
CLARA: What are they?

105
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:53,120
DOCTOR: I haven't a clue.
Isn't that exciting?

106
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:02,080
Where did they go?

107
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,480
What is it, some kind of submarine?

108
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:08,760
No, it's alien.

109
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:45,280
DOCTOR: That's weird.
The Tardis hasn't translated it.

110
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:47,640
(WHOOSHING)

111
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:50,440
(WHISPERING) Hey, look! They're back.

112
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:57,480
Hello, did you want to show us this?

113
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:59,360
It's very nice.

114
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,280
(INAUDIBLE)

115
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:04,720
Wait, are they saying something?

116
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:14,920
OK, they now appear
to be arming themselves.

117
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,080
Yes, I spotted that too.

118
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:19,320
Was it something she said?
She does that.

119
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:20,920
She once had an argument with Gandhi!

120
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:23,720
I'm starting to see
why the crew did a runner.

121
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,480
(CLANKING)

122
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:37,720
(GASPS)

123
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:39,880
(INAUDIBLE)

124
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:47,720
CLARA: Run!

125
00:08:51,760 --> 00:08:53,320
In here! Quick!

126
00:08:57,560 --> 00:08:58,840
(GASPING)

127
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:01,600
(INAUDIBLE)

128
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:08,960
DOCTOR: What are you?

129
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:15,120
Who the hell are you
and what are you doing here?

130
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:17,000
This is Clara.

131
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:19,360
And I'm the Doctor.

132
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:22,600
-You're from UNIT.
-Well, if that's what it says.

133
00:09:22,680 --> 00:09:24,560
I'm Pritchard. This is Bennett.

134
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:26,000
O'Donnell!

135
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:28,240
(CHUCKLES) You're really the Doctor?
I'm a huge fan.

136
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,480
(LAUGHS)

137
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:34,120
Uh, I mean, um, you know, nice work.

138
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:37,160
Tim Lunn, I sign for Cass.

139
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:40,000
Tell me, what about
those things out there, what are they?

140
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:42,040
Why are they trying to kill us?

141
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:44,840
Well, they're, uh, they're ghosts.

142
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:46,400
They're not ghosts.

143
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:48,120
-Cass is saying a...
-Thank you,

144
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,840
but I actually don't need your help.

145
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:52,440
I can speak sign. Go ahead.

146
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:02,000
Wait, no, no, actually, I can't.

147
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:05,080
It's been deleted for semaphore.

148
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:07,240
Someone get me a selection of flags.

149
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:10,520
"One of the ghosts is our previous
commanding officer.

150
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:13,880
"The other, moley-guy,
we don't know what he is."”

151
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:15,200
He's from the planet Tivoli.

152
00:10:15,280 --> 00:10:17,360
See? I told you he was an alien.

153
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:19,040
Didn't I say that?

154
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:21,160
Weird thing is, they're not violent.

155
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,480
They're too cowardly.

156
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:25,040
They wouldn't say boo to a goose.

157
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:28,120
More like to give the goose
their car keys and bank details.

158
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:29,720
When did they first appear?

159
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:32,040
Oh, did you see
that spaceship in the hangar?

160
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:33,560
Yeah, we found that on the lake bed.

161
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:34,640
We just got it on board

162
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:37,160
and one of the engines started up
and then Moran got...

163
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:40,360
Moran was killed.

164
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,400
"Then, they appeared

165
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:44,560
"and pretty much straightaway
started trying to kill us.

166
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:47,000
"So, we grabbed what we could
and were looking for somewhere to hide,

167
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:50,760
"and that's when we realised
the ghosts couldn't come in here."

168
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:53,400
-What is this place?
-It's a Faraday cage.

169
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:56,120
Completely impenetrable
to radio waves and, apparently,

170
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:58,680
whatever those things are out there.

171
00:10:58,760 --> 00:11:00,280
So, who's in charge now?

172
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:03,200
-I need to know who to ignore.
-That'd be me.

173
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:05,160
Her.

174
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:09,080
Actually, that would be me.
I represent Vector Petroleum.

175
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:11,800
-We own the mining rights to the oil.
-The oil?

176
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:13,800
Where are we?

177
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:16,560
Uh, this used to be
a military training site.

178
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:18,760
Uh, there was a, a dam overlooking it,

179
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:21,160
but the dam burst
and the valley was submerged.

180
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:24,080
Then 20 years ago, we discovered
a massive oil reservoir underneath it.

181
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:26,000
COMPUTER VOICE: Good morning.
Entering day mode.

182
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:28,800
OK, it's morning.
We can go outside now.

183
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:29,960
LUNN: Thank God for that.

184
00:11:30,040 --> 00:11:31,480
PRITCHARD: At last,
we can get out of here.

185
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:34,960
Morning?

186
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:37,640
Yeah, uh, we're too far below
the surface for daylight,

187
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:40,200
so we have to demarcate
artificial days and nights.

188
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:42,640
Um, I'd like to have
a look at that spaceship,

189
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:45,040
but what about those things
that aren't ghosts?

190
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:46,840
Oh, it's all right,
they only come out at night.

191
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:51,320
Weird how that is not comforting.

192
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:56,600
If whatever they are...

193
00:11:56,680 --> 00:11:57,840
-They're ghosts.
-They're not ghosts!

194
00:11:57,920 --> 00:12:00,080
...have been trying to kill you,
why haven't you abandoned the base?

195
00:12:00,160 --> 00:12:01,160
That was my call.

196
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:03,720
We've got about a trillion dollars'
worth of mining equipment here.

197
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:05,560
We're not just going to abandon it.

198
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:08,120
What? If it all goes pear-shaped,

199
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:10,200
it's not them that lose their bonus.

200
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:16,240
It's OK, I understand.
You're an idiot.

201
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:20,440
Come to mention it,
why is there a Faraday cage on the base?

202
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:23,440
It's the, uh, mining equipment.
It runs on nuclear fission.

203
00:12:23,520 --> 00:12:25,320
The Faraday cage
has been lined with lead

204
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:28,000
to act as a shelter
in the event of a radiation leak.

205
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:31,040
So, we are fighting
an unknown homicidal force

206
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:34,360
that has taken the form of your
commanding officer and a cowardly alien,

207
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:37,120
underwater, in a nuclear reactor?

208
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:39,840
Anything else I should know? Has someone
got a peanut allergy or something?

209
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:40,920
(CHUCKLES)

210
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:45,760
It all started with this ship.

211
00:12:45,880 --> 00:12:47,480
This is where the answer will be.

212
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:08,160
What's happened
to the stuff you've removed?

213
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,440
This is for long-haul flights.

214
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:13,560
There should be
a suspended animation chamber

215
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:15,280
for the pilot, right here.

216
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:18,120
-Plus, a power cell is missing.
-Power cell?

217
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:20,600
Yeah, you can see the casing is empty.

218
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:25,160
It's not safe out here!

219
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:26,640
CLARA: What's the matter?

220
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:28,240
She won't let me look
inside the spaceship.

221
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:31,000
-She says it's not safe.
-I'm saying it's not safe out here.

222
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:32,200
I imagine they're pretty valuable.

223
00:13:32,280 --> 00:13:33,600
-What?
-PRITCHARD: I mean powerful.

224
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:35,960
I imagine those power cells
are pretty powerful.

225
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:38,400
They can zap a vessel from
one side of the galaxy to the other,

226
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:40,200
so, you take
a wild stab in the dark.

227
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:41,960
And the missing one
must still be out there.

228
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:43,800
Yes, well, otherwise... Sorry.

229
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:45,440
Why is this man still talking to me?

230
00:13:45,520 --> 00:13:48,120
We haven't removed anything.
There hasn't been time.

231
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,280
DOCTOR: So what have we got?

232
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:55,920
Moran dies and then those things appear.

233
00:13:58,480 --> 00:14:00,240
They can walk through walls.

234
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:04,800
They only come out at night.

235
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:08,000
And they're sort of see-through.

236
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:10,160
CLARA: Doctor, wait,
you're not saying...

237
00:14:11,480 --> 00:14:13,520
They're ghosts.

238
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:15,440
Yeah, ghosts!

239
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:17,280
CLARA: You said there was no such thing.

240
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:19,360
You actually pooh-poohed
the ghost theory.

241
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:22,400
Yes, well... Well,
there was no such thing

242
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:26,680
as socks or smart phones
and badgers until there suddenly were.

243
00:14:26,760 --> 00:14:29,160
Besides, what else could they be?

244
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:30,440
They're not holograms.

245
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:31,760
They're not Flesh Avatars.

246
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:33,000
They're not Autons.

247
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:36,360
They're not digital copies
bouncing around the Nethersphere.

248
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:40,440
No, these people are literally,
actually dead!

249
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:42,480
Wow!

250
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:46,800
This is... It's amazing!

251
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:48,960
I've never actually met a proper ghost!

252
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:50,520
(MOUTHING)

253
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,480
"Moran was our friend."

254
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,200
(WHISPERING) The cards.

255
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:01,600
Oh! Oh, right you are. Uh...

256
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:04,680
(SIGHS) Come here.

257
00:15:09,920 --> 00:15:11,400
(CLEARS THROAT)

258
00:15:12,880 --> 00:15:13,960
(CLEARS THROAT)

259
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:16,680
I'm very sorry for your loss.

260
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:19,680
I'll do all I can
to solve the death of your

261
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:23,040
friend, slash family member, slash pet.

262
00:15:29,880 --> 00:15:31,520
But don't you see what this means?

263
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:35,560
Death, it was the one thing that unified

264
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:38,000
every single living creature
in the universe,

265
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:39,080
and now it's gone!

266
00:15:41,720 --> 00:15:42,920
How can you just sit there?

267
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,640
Don't you want
to go out there right now,

268
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,400
wrestle them to the ground
and ask them questions

269
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:47,800
until your throat falls out?

270
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:49,560
What's death like? Does it hurt?

271
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:50,920
Do you still get hungry?

272
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:54,000
Do you miss being alive?

273
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:57,880
Why can you only handle metal objects?
Oh, I didn't know I'd noticed that.

274
00:15:57,960 --> 00:16:00,240
OK, so they'll try
to kill you, blah, blah, blah.

275
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:02,880
What does that matter? You come back!

276
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:04,880
A bit murdery, sure, but even so!

277
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:08,080
Calm, Doctor, calm.

278
00:16:08,160 --> 00:16:10,440
You were like this
when you met Shirley Bassey.

279
00:16:10,960 --> 00:16:11,960
OK.

280
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:16,240
Question one. What is a ghost?

281
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:19,280
Question two. What do they want?

282
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:22,320
Whoa, whoa, what's happening?

283
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:29,000
COMPUTER VOICE: Good evening.
Entering night mode.

284
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:32,080
That's not right. We're switching back
into night mode again.

285
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:33,280
This can't happen.

286
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:34,960
No. No. No.

287
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:38,120
-(BELL TOLLING)
-BENNETT: Um, what's doing that?

288
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:40,120
(BELL CONTINUES TOLLING)

289
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:44,200
CLARA: Doctor?

290
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:46,480
DOCTOR: The Tardis Cloister Bell!

291
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:48,120
(BELL CONTINUES TOLLING)

292
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:49,720
CLARA: Doctor, what's wrong?

293
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:53,280
DOCTOR: It must be the ghosts.

294
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:56,000
That's why she was upset
when we got here.

295
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:58,040
Why? I don't understand.

296
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:00,880
It was just what I was saying.

297
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:03,560
You live and you die, that's it.

298
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:05,240
The ghosts are aberrations.

299
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:08,160
A splinter of time in the skin.

300
00:17:09,120 --> 00:17:10,800
They're unnatural.

301
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:13,600
She wants to get away from them.

302
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:15,080
So what do we do?

303
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:19,400
Put the hand brake on.

304
00:17:25,840 --> 00:17:27,520
Whoa, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho!

305
00:17:27,600 --> 00:17:29,480
Where do you think you're going?

306
00:17:29,560 --> 00:17:31,040
Out there, where the action is.

307
00:17:31,120 --> 00:17:32,480
Look, um...

308
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:34,920
-What?
-Oh. This is my own fault.

309
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:39,400
I like adventures
as much as the next man.

310
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:40,800
If the next man is a man
who likes adventures.

311
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:43,240
Even so, don't... Don't go native.

312
00:17:43,320 --> 00:17:45,600
(CHUCKLES) What do you mean? I'm not.

313
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:49,280
Look, there's a whole dimension in here.

314
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:53,200
But there's only room for one me.

315
00:17:55,120 --> 00:17:56,360
Wait. Wait a second.

316
00:17:56,440 --> 00:17:59,240
You just raved about ghosts like a kid
who had too much sherbet.

317
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:00,760
Do you know what you need?
You need a hobby!

318
00:18:00,840 --> 00:18:02,000
(LAUGHS) I really don't.

319
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:03,680
DOCTOR: Or even better,
another relationship!

320
00:18:03,760 --> 00:18:06,360
Come on, you lot,
you're bananas about relationships.

321
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:09,320
You're always writing songs about them

322
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:11,640
or going to war or getting tattooed.

323
00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:13,960
Doctor. I'm fine.

324
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:20,600
I just felt that I had to say something.

325
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:22,880
I know, and I appreciated it.

326
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:26,960
-'Cause I've got a duty of care.
-Which you take very seriously, I know.

327
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:29,720
-So can stop now?
-Please.

328
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:31,480
Please do. (CHUCKLES)

329
00:18:39,760 --> 00:18:41,040
O'DONNELL: (ON PA) Attention all crew.

330
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:42,600
The Drum switched to night mode early,

331
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:45,240
so grab provisions
and make your way to the Faraday cage.

332
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:52,320
PRITCHARD: That you, Bennett?

333
00:18:53,680 --> 00:18:56,600
I went out
looking for that missing power cell.

334
00:18:56,680 --> 00:19:00,800
OK, contractually it's a grey area,

335
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:04,640
but I reckon we can argue
everything non-indigenous is an asset

336
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:05,760
and therefore...

337
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:08,560
(WATER DRIPPING)

338
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:12,080
Bennett?

339
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:15,400
(GASPS)

340
00:19:17,280 --> 00:19:19,680
-We're meant to be in day mode!
-(INAUDIBLE)

341
00:19:19,880 --> 00:19:21,840
You shouldn't be here.

342
00:19:38,680 --> 00:19:39,680
What?

343
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:42,800
What?

344
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:44,120
What are you saying?

345
00:19:47,120 --> 00:19:49,480
-No, Moran! Don't!
-(BEEPING)

346
00:19:49,560 --> 00:19:50,560
(GASPS)

347
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:56,240
O'DONNELL: (ON PA)
Pritchard, you are unaccounted for.

348
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:59,920
Contact the bridge or get to
the Faraday cage immediately.

349
00:20:00,920 --> 00:20:04,960
Pritchard! Contact the bridge,
or get to the Faraday cage!

350
00:20:05,040 --> 00:20:06,160
BENNETT: I'd love to work for UNIT.

351
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:09,240
Earth's first line of defence and all.

352
00:20:09,320 --> 00:20:10,680
Yeah. I'm probably not suited though.

353
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:15,000
Not much of a fighter.
Uh, more of a bleeder.

354
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:20,920
CLARA: Pritchard! Where have you been?
Everyone's been looking for you.

355
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:23,560
-What's with the wet suit?
-Yeah, where've you been?

356
00:20:24,280 --> 00:20:26,920
BENNETT: O'Donnell it's OK
Pritchard's in here!

357
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:30,440
Pritchard, you moron, grab your stuff,
we're locking down early.

358
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:32,640
In case I can't get this back
into day mode.

359
00:20:34,720 --> 00:20:35,840
CLARA: Is he all right?

360
00:20:36,160 --> 00:20:37,160
-(THUD)
-(BOTH GASP)

361
00:20:38,680 --> 00:20:39,680
BENNETT: Man overboard.

362
00:20:40,320 --> 00:20:42,120
Man overboard! We need a rescue team!

363
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:43,920
Bennett, wait! It's Pritchard!

364
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:04,600
He's a ghost.

365
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:05,840
He's another ghost.

366
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:15,680
O'DONNELL: Come on. Come on.

367
00:21:18,560 --> 00:21:21,440
Come on, come on, come on, come on!

368
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:27,800
-COMPUTER VOICE: Good morning.
-(EXHALES)

369
00:21:27,880 --> 00:21:29,320
Entering day mode.

370
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:32,160
No, no, Moran! Don't!

371
00:21:32,440 --> 00:21:33,640
(BEEP)

372
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:43,960
They're working out
how to use the base against us.

373
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:48,720
Altering the time settings
so they can go about uninhibited,

374
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:50,640
opening the airlocks.

375
00:21:50,720 --> 00:21:51,760
They're learning.

376
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:54,000
And now there's three of them?

377
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:56,800
Cass, what do we do?

378
00:21:59,640 --> 00:22:01,080
"We abandon the base.

379
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:03,600
"Topside can send down
a whole team of marines

380
00:22:03,680 --> 00:22:04,960
"or Ghostbusters or whatever."

381
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:06,360
Wait, wait!

382
00:22:06,440 --> 00:22:07,840
"I can't force you to leave,

383
00:22:09,560 --> 00:22:11,520
"so you can stay and do the whole

384
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:13,080
"The Cabin in the Woods thing

385
00:22:13,160 --> 00:22:15,880
"and get killed or drowned if you want.

386
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:19,800
"But my first priority
is to protect my crew.”

387
00:22:25,360 --> 00:22:28,200
(WHISPERING) Yeah,
but we're coming back, aren't we?

388
00:22:28,960 --> 00:22:30,120
(WHISPERS) Yes, we're coming back.

389
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:32,640
"O'Donnell, tell them
we're abandoning base on my orders."

390
00:22:32,720 --> 00:22:35,120
Topside, Topside,
this is Lance Corporal Alice O'Donnell

391
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:36,560
from Drum Control. Over.

392
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:38,960
MAN: (ON RADIO)
Drum Control, this is Topside.

393
00:22:39,040 --> 00:22:40,360
We have received your message,

394
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:42,080
submarine on its way. Over.

395
00:22:42,720 --> 00:22:44,240
O'DONNELL: Repeat, Topside. Over.

396
00:22:44,320 --> 00:22:46,240
We've received your request
for a rescue sub,

397
00:22:46,320 --> 00:22:47,720
it's two minutes away. Over.

398
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:49,160
Topside, who did you speak to,

399
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:51,040
and when was this request made? Over.

400
00:22:51,120 --> 00:22:53,000
Drum Control, it was in Morse code.

401
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:54,840
Arrived maybe half an hour ago.

402
00:22:54,920 --> 00:22:57,120
Said it was urgent, comms were down,

403
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:59,040
two crew members critically il

404
00:22:59,120 --> 00:23:01,720
full paramedic team requested. Over.

405
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:04,120
Topside, this is the Doctor,

406
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:06,520
UNIT security visa 7-1-0 Apple 0-0.

407
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:07,640
You may be familiar with my work.

408
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:08,760
Call back the sub.

409
00:23:08,840 --> 00:23:10,400
-Doctor, why...
-DOCTOR: Call it back!

410
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:13,240
We have a hazardous
and undefined contagion on board.

411
00:23:13,320 --> 00:23:15,960
This base is now under quarantine.

412
00:23:16,840 --> 00:23:18,360
What did you do that for?

413
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:20,640
Well, none of us sent
the message, did we?

414
00:23:20,720 --> 00:23:22,120
So that means that the ghosts sent it.

415
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:24,640
Which means they want
that crew down here.

416
00:23:24,720 --> 00:23:25,760
"Why would they do that?"

417
00:23:25,840 --> 00:23:27,160
Well, I don't know,
but I'm pretty certain it's not

418
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:28,480
so they can all form a boy band.

419
00:23:29,240 --> 00:23:32,160
OK, we solve this on our own.

420
00:23:32,240 --> 00:23:33,320
The ghosts can only come out at night

421
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:36,160
so they change the base's
time settings, why?

422
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:38,600
-What's different at night?
-It's mainly atmospheric.

423
00:23:38,680 --> 00:23:40,920
The lights are dim,
the noise from the engines is muffled.

424
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:42,440
No, something... Something else.

425
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:46,440
"The diagnostic sweep,
when the systems are checked.

426
00:23:46,520 --> 00:23:47,800
"That stops at night to save power."”

427
00:23:47,880 --> 00:23:49,480
What systems, specifically?

428
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:51,840
Life support, the locks.
They're electromagnetic.

429
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:53,640
They have to be
secured in case of flooding,

430
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:56,640
so throughout the day they're checked
one by one, every few seconds.

431
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:02,360
(SIGHS) The answer's
in there somewhere, I can smell it.

432
00:24:03,040 --> 00:24:05,080
Doctor, what do we do?

433
00:24:07,080 --> 00:24:09,800
O'Donnell. Excellent work.

434
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:13,720
Returning the base to day mode.

435
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:15,800
(SHEEPISHLY) Shut up. It was nothing.

436
00:24:17,080 --> 00:24:19,000
-You really think so?
-Now put it back into night mode.

437
00:24:19,080 --> 00:24:20,680
-What?
-We know nothing!

438
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:23,240
We don't know what they want.

439
00:24:23,320 --> 00:24:24,600
That's what's getting us killed.

440
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:27,160
Well, I won't run. Not any more.

441
00:24:27,840 --> 00:24:31,640
So, O'Donnell, kindly put the base
back into night mode.

442
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:34,040
We want to know what
these ghosts are after,

443
00:24:34,120 --> 00:24:35,440
we ask them.

444
00:24:35,520 --> 00:24:38,600
We are going to do the impossible.
Capture a ghost.

445
00:24:38,680 --> 00:24:40,000
(BEEPING)

446
00:24:40,280 --> 00:24:42,080
(CLUNKING)

447
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:47,440
COMPUTER VOICE: Good evening,
entering night mode.

448
00:24:58,360 --> 00:24:59,520
(SHUDDERING)

449
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:02,200
Hey, how's it going?

450
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:05,240
(WHIMPERING)

451
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:10,960
Bennett's got them moving
and Clara's in position.

452
00:25:11,040 --> 00:25:13,280
Clara, Bennett is gonna run
across the top of the T-junction

453
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:15,040
to your right in about ten seconds.

454
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:17,720
Draw the ghosts towards you.

455
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:20,680
Turn right, and then take second left.

456
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:27,920
Hey! Hey, ghosts.

457
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:29,000
Down here!

458
00:25:33,680 --> 00:25:35,560
DOCTOR: Lunn, they're coming your way.

459
00:25:35,640 --> 00:25:37,480
Clara's going to duck down to her left.

460
00:25:37,560 --> 00:25:41,440
You're gonna keep the ghosts
going on the same route they are on now.

461
00:25:41,520 --> 00:25:43,680
Then, after about 50 yards,
on your left there's a flood door.

462
00:25:43,760 --> 00:25:46,440
O'Donnell will close the door
once you're through.

463
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:50,320
I...I can hear them.

464
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:52,520
Lunn. Don't let them see where you go.

465
00:25:58,600 --> 00:25:59,960
(PANTING)

466
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:01,920
(GASPS)

467
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:05,960
Hey. Yeah, this way.

468
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:11,480
We've got a problem!

469
00:26:11,560 --> 00:26:12,840
They've separated.

470
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:14,920
What?

471
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:17,680
O'DONNELL: Moran and the mole guy
are going after Clara.

472
00:26:19,320 --> 00:26:21,640
O'DONNELL: Clara, look out.
Two ghosts are still on your case.

473
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:22,720
Right behind you.

474
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:28,240
I'm beginning to think we should have
let the ghosts in on the plan.

475
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:30,400
Clara, there's a flood door
at the end of the corridor

476
00:26:30,480 --> 00:26:32,120
around the corner to your right.

477
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:33,720
We'll close it from here.

478
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:35,240
Listen to me.

479
00:26:35,320 --> 00:26:36,400
You've got to get through that door

480
00:26:36,480 --> 00:26:37,960
before Moran
and the other ghost sees you.

481
00:26:42,640 --> 00:26:43,640
CLARA: Doctor!

482
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:45,040
DOCTOR: Now, O'Donnell! Fast as you can.

483
00:26:45,120 --> 00:26:46,480
(BEEPING)

484
00:26:49,320 --> 00:26:50,360
(CLANGING)

485
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:58,200
Guys, I'm nearly at my door.

486
00:27:02,680 --> 00:27:03,880
Now, Lunn. Quickly.

487
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:11,000
It saw me.

488
00:27:11,440 --> 00:27:13,400
Oh, God. It saw me.

489
00:27:16,600 --> 00:27:17,720
It's coming through.

490
00:27:20,080 --> 00:27:21,400
It's coming through the door!

491
00:27:22,360 --> 00:27:25,400
-We don't have a camera in there.
-Lunn, can you hear me?

492
00:27:25,480 --> 00:27:26,760
Can you hear me?

493
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:30,320
Lunn, what's happening?

494
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:33,040
(GROANS)

495
00:27:33,880 --> 00:27:34,880
(SHUDDERING)

496
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:55,440
(CLATTERING)

497
00:27:58,440 --> 00:28:01,360
DOCTOR: Lunn! Can you hear me?
Lunn! Lunn!

498
00:28:01,880 --> 00:28:04,120
Can you hear me? Lunn! Lunn!

499
00:28:04,200 --> 00:28:05,880
Lunn!
What's happening? Lunn!

500
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:08,440
-Lunn, can you hear me?
-I'm OK.

501
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:10,880
Cass. He's alive.

502
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:12,880
LUNN: 7t didn't hurt me. I'm OK.

503
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:15,440
What? What's wrong with you?
Why didn't it hurt you?

504
00:28:15,520 --> 00:28:16,760
Bennett, you're on again.

505
00:28:16,840 --> 00:28:18,560
-Bennett, where are you?
-(BEEPING)

506
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:20,360
O'DONNELL: There.

507
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,240
Oh, God, look.

508
00:28:23,320 --> 00:28:24,320
Bennett, can you hear me?

509
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:26,720
There are two ghosts
Just around the corner from you.

510
00:28:26,800 --> 00:28:28,280
(WHISPERS) Yes, thanks, I'd noticed.

511
00:28:28,360 --> 00:28:30,200
The Faraday cage
is across the intersection

512
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:31,400
and down the corridor to your right.

513
00:28:31,480 --> 00:28:33,000
This last bit is down to you.

514
00:28:40,800 --> 00:28:41,920
(GRUNTS)

515
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:50,280
OK, so, the good news is
they aren't split up any more.

516
00:28:52,640 --> 00:28:53,840
Cue Clara!

517
00:28:58,480 --> 00:29:00,880
(STATIC CRACKLING)

518
00:29:05,680 --> 00:29:06,880
We need to talk.

519
00:29:08,160 --> 00:29:09,440
Sorry, chaps. Just a hologram.

520
00:29:09,520 --> 00:29:11,200
You play a little bit too rough.

521
00:29:20,120 --> 00:29:24,560
I'm fine, by the way.
In case any of you were worried.

522
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:26,000
Cass, are you seeing this?

523
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:29,520
O'DONNELL: Sonic glasses Wi-Fi
locked in. On screen B2.

524
00:29:35,640 --> 00:29:37,240
She says she can't see them properly.

525
00:29:37,320 --> 00:29:39,720
"The glass is too thick
and they're too far away."

526
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:42,560
-Open the door.
-What?

527
00:29:43,200 --> 00:29:46,000
Doctor, you can't go in there.
They will kill you!

528
00:29:46,080 --> 00:29:48,200
They don't have any weapons
or access to any of the controls.

529
00:29:48,280 --> 00:29:51,400
They can't hurt me. So open the door.

530
00:29:55,240 --> 00:29:56,240
(BEEPING)

531
00:29:56,400 --> 00:29:57,720
(DOOR OPENS)

532
00:30:13,520 --> 00:30:15,160
(WHISPERS) Cold...

533
00:30:16,240 --> 00:30:17,320
(NORMAL VOICE) ..isn't it?

534
00:30:17,400 --> 00:30:19,920
Take your weapons away
and you're not so scary, are you?

535
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:21,960
That better, Cass?

536
00:30:28,240 --> 00:30:30,440
She says they're saying the same thing,

537
00:30:30,520 --> 00:30:32,440
the same phrase, over and over.

538
00:30:35,320 --> 00:30:36,960
They're saying,

539
00:30:37,040 --> 00:30:39,960
"The dark... The score...

540
00:30:41,040 --> 00:30:42,480
"No, the sword...

541
00:30:43,320 --> 00:30:44,520
"The for sale?

542
00:30:47,120 --> 00:30:49,200
"No, the forsaken. The temple."

543
00:30:49,720 --> 00:30:51,200
-What?
-LUNN: Yes, she's sure.

544
00:30:51,280 --> 00:30:53,920
"'The Dark. The Sword.
The Forsaken. The Temple.'

545
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:57,560
"lust that. Over and over.”

546
00:30:57,640 --> 00:31:00,680
Dark. Sword. Forsaken. Temple.

547
00:31:00,760 --> 00:31:02,520
What does that mean?
What are you telling me, big man?

548
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:08,800
Bennett. I need maps!

549
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:11,640
I think I just worked out
what our friend here is telling us.

550
00:31:12,080 --> 00:31:13,520
DOCTOR: They're coordinates.

551
00:31:13,600 --> 00:31:15,480
BENNETT: How can they be coordinates?

552
00:31:17,080 --> 00:31:19,040
The Dark... Space.

553
00:31:20,120 --> 00:31:23,480
So, whoever's following the coordinates
knows they're going to another planet.

554
00:31:23,960 --> 00:31:25,360
The Sword...

555
00:31:31,760 --> 00:31:35,240
Orion's sword.

556
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:36,920
The sword, the three stars,

557
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:39,640
although one isn't actually a star
but the Orion nebula

558
00:31:39,720 --> 00:31:43,000
hanging down from Orion's Belt. But...

559
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:46,360
If viewed from back here,

560
00:31:47,880 --> 00:31:50,280
the Earth becomes
the fourth bit of the sword.

561
00:31:50,360 --> 00:31:52,640
So, narrowed it down to a planet now.

562
00:31:52,840 --> 00:31:54,040
Getting closer!

563
00:31:55,040 --> 00:31:56,160
The Forsaken...

564
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:01,160
The forsaken or abandoned or empty town.

565
00:32:01,240 --> 00:32:02,240
See, it's a location,

566
00:32:02,320 --> 00:32:06,200
beaming out to someone
or something across the universe,

567
00:32:06,280 --> 00:32:07,560
over and over.

568
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:10,040
-Every time they kill one of us...
-It strengthens the signal.

569
00:32:10,480 --> 00:32:11,920
Another ghost, another transmitter.

570
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:13,680
Which is why they sent
for that rescue sub.

571
00:32:13,800 --> 00:32:15,880
Get more people down here. Kill them.

572
00:32:15,960 --> 00:32:18,800
Make even more ghosts
to beam out the coordinates.

573
00:32:19,680 --> 00:32:21,600
"But why are they beaming out
the coordinates?

574
00:32:21,680 --> 00:32:23,080
"Is it a distress call?"

575
00:32:23,160 --> 00:32:24,160
It could be.

576
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:26,680
Or a warning.

577
00:32:26,760 --> 00:32:28,160
Might even be a call to arms.

578
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:31,040
It could mean "Come here,
they're vulnerable, help yourself."

579
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:35,200
Wait a minute, though.

580
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:38,800
Wait a minuet. You know what this means?

581
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:41,640
It means that they're not
a natural phenomenon.

582
00:32:41,720 --> 00:32:45,920
It means that someone
is deliberately getting people killed,

583
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:48,960
high jacking their souls
and turning them into transmitters.

584
00:32:49,040 --> 00:32:50,840
But what do the coordinates
lead to, though?

585
00:32:50,920 --> 00:32:52,000
To us? To the ghosts, what?

586
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:54,680
Ah! What the coordinates are for.

587
00:32:54,760 --> 00:32:57,600
That is part of the answer to the other
question you're all thinking.

588
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:04,480
Really? Come on, none of you?

589
00:33:04,560 --> 00:33:07,160
Surely, just being around me
makes you cleverer by osmosis!

590
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:08,720
What is the other question?

591
00:33:11,160 --> 00:33:14,160
"The Temple.
The fourth part of the directions.

592
00:33:14,240 --> 00:33:15,520
"What's the Temple?"

593
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:17,760
Finally. It's like pulling teeth.

594
00:33:17,840 --> 00:33:19,840
This is the flooded military town.

595
00:33:19,920 --> 00:33:22,480
Shops, houses, a town square,
and this...

596
00:33:22,560 --> 00:33:23,640
A church!

597
00:33:23,720 --> 00:33:26,560
Whatever the coordinates
are for, it's in that church.

598
00:33:26,640 --> 00:33:29,840
Find that and you're a hop, skip
and a jump to stopping them.

599
00:33:29,920 --> 00:33:32,040
Wait, you're not suggesting that...

600
00:33:33,680 --> 00:33:35,560
But we're safe now.

601
00:33:35,640 --> 00:33:38,440
The ghosts are in the cage,
we can get out of here.

602
00:33:39,040 --> 00:33:42,440
No one has to stay.
In fact, I would prefer it if you went.

603
00:33:42,520 --> 00:33:45,720
You'll get in the way and ask
ridiculous questions. But...

604
00:33:46,280 --> 00:33:49,760
You know, you have chosen
to protect and serve.

605
00:33:49,840 --> 00:33:53,960
You have given yourself
to science and the pursuit of knowledge.

606
00:33:54,040 --> 00:33:58,480
None of you have chosen
anonymous or selfish lives.

607
00:33:58,720 --> 00:34:01,600
Go, and a part of you
will always wonder,

608
00:34:01,680 --> 00:34:03,480
"What would have happened if I'd stayed?

609
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:07,120
"How could I have helped?
What would I have learned?”

610
00:34:07,200 --> 00:34:09,040
I want you to go.

611
00:34:09,120 --> 00:34:11,160
But you should know
what it is that you're leaving.

612
00:34:13,920 --> 00:34:15,480
Cass says we should go,

613
00:34:16,320 --> 00:34:19,560
but everything that happens here
is her responsibility now...

614
00:34:19,640 --> 00:34:21,080
So she's going to stay.

615
00:34:23,520 --> 00:34:26,480
So I, uh, guess I should, too.

616
00:34:26,560 --> 00:34:28,360
Oh, count me in.

617
00:34:28,440 --> 00:34:29,720
Who wants to live forever, anyway?

618
00:34:30,040 --> 00:34:33,120
Sorry, um, have you gone insane?

619
00:34:33,200 --> 00:34:34,560
We can go home.

620
00:34:41,040 --> 00:34:42,560
They're ghosts though.

621
00:34:44,200 --> 00:34:45,680
How can they be ghosts?

622
00:34:49,160 --> 00:34:50,640
Well, at least if I die,

623
00:34:50,720 --> 00:34:53,800
you know I really will
come back and haunt you, all.

624
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:05,440
BENNETT: OK,
the sub is approaching the town square.

625
00:35:05,520 --> 00:35:06,520
Which way is the church?

626
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:09,160
O'DONNELL: North-northwest, 150 yards.

627
00:35:11,240 --> 00:35:13,760
That's it. Starboard, 2 degrees.

628
00:35:19,920 --> 00:35:21,720
CLARA: What are we looking for, exactly?

629
00:35:21,800 --> 00:35:23,800
DOCTOR: Something that has
the power to raise the dead

630
00:35:23,880 --> 00:35:25,400
and turn them into transmitters.

631
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:27,080
I expect we'll know it when we see it.

632
00:35:27,160 --> 00:35:28,680
BENNETT: Wait, I've found the church.

633
00:35:32,120 --> 00:35:34,160
DOCTOR: That's it, keep going.

634
00:35:44,240 --> 00:35:45,640
Wait...

635
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:47,800
What's that?

636
00:35:50,200 --> 00:35:51,400
Move closer.

637
00:35:59,920 --> 00:36:02,520
It's the suspended animation chamber
from the spaceship.

638
00:36:04,280 --> 00:36:05,840
So the pilot could be in there.

639
00:36:10,120 --> 00:36:11,800
There's something inside there.

640
00:36:12,840 --> 00:36:15,280
But it's dead-lock sealed,
I can't open it.

641
00:36:15,960 --> 00:36:18,480
It should be the pilot, it should be.

642
00:36:18,560 --> 00:36:20,080
So why do I think it isn't?

643
00:36:20,160 --> 00:36:21,560
More questions.

644
00:36:21,640 --> 00:36:24,360
Everything I solve, just more questions.

645
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:27,440
I have to go back to the beginning.

646
00:36:30,160 --> 00:36:32,640
We arrive, we see the ghosts.
They don't kill us.

647
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:35,880
They lead us here,
they show us the spaceship.

648
00:36:37,080 --> 00:36:38,440
Then they try to kill us.

649
00:36:56,840 --> 00:36:58,920
Not translated by the Tardis. Why?

650
00:37:08,480 --> 00:37:09,960
Lunn, translate for me.

651
00:37:11,080 --> 00:37:12,520
Whenever I step outside,

652
00:37:12,600 --> 00:37:14,560
you are the smartest person in the room.

653
00:37:14,640 --> 00:37:17,640
So, tell me. What's weird about this?

654
00:37:18,400 --> 00:37:19,880
I know that it's all bonkers,

655
00:37:19,960 --> 00:37:22,240
but, you know, when you think about it,

656
00:37:22,320 --> 00:37:24,840
one thing keeps snagging
in your mind. What is it?

657
00:37:30,200 --> 00:37:32,000
"The markings on the inside
of the spaceship.”

658
00:37:32,080 --> 00:37:36,680
The markings on the inside
of the spaceship. Yes!

659
00:37:37,440 --> 00:37:38,680
Why?

660
00:37:39,760 --> 00:37:41,280
-"I don't think they're just words."
-They're not.

661
00:37:41,360 --> 00:37:42,640
They're magnets.

662
00:37:42,720 --> 00:37:44,440
Magnets, how?

663
00:37:44,520 --> 00:37:49,000
Well, a localised and manufactured
electromagnetic field to be precise.

664
00:37:49,800 --> 00:37:53,920
The dark. The sword.
The forsaken. The temple.

665
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:56,320
When we heard the coordinates
for the first time,

666
00:37:56,400 --> 00:37:58,680
did anyone expect them not to be that?

667
00:37:59,280 --> 00:38:01,560
No, exactly. Me neither.

668
00:38:01,640 --> 00:38:04,320
It's like we already knew somehow.

669
00:38:04,480 --> 00:38:06,080
Like the words were already in us.

670
00:38:06,840 --> 00:38:09,680
So that writing is the coordinates?

671
00:38:10,080 --> 00:38:14,080
Everything we see
or experience shapes us in some way.

672
00:38:15,280 --> 00:38:19,000
But these words actually rewrite
the synaptic connections in your brain.

673
00:38:19,080 --> 00:38:22,000
They literally change the way
you are wired.

674
00:38:23,120 --> 00:38:26,800
Clara, why don't I have
a radio in the Tardis?

675
00:38:27,400 --> 00:38:30,000
You took it apart and used the pieces
to make a clockwork squirrel.

676
00:38:30,840 --> 00:38:34,520
And because whatever song
I heard first thing in the morning,

677
00:38:34,600 --> 00:38:35,600
I was stuck with.

678
00:38:36,680 --> 00:38:39,400
Two weeks of
Mysterious Girl by Peter Andre.

679
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:41,800
I was begging for the brush
of death's merciful hand.

680
00:38:42,640 --> 00:38:46,120
Don't you see?
These words are an ear-worm.

681
00:38:47,240 --> 00:38:51,040
A song you can't stop humming
even after you die.

682
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:54,880
CLARA: OK,
so the spaceship lands here.

683
00:38:54,960 --> 00:38:56,440
The pilot leaves the writing on the wall

684
00:38:56,520 --> 00:38:58,360
so whoever sees it, when they die,

685
00:38:58,440 --> 00:38:59,920
they become a beacon of the coordinates,

686
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:02,880
while he, slash she, slash it

687
00:39:02,960 --> 00:39:04,920
snoozes in the suspended
animation chamber.

688
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:08,440
Waiting for his, slash her,
slash its mates to pick the message up.

689
00:39:10,400 --> 00:39:11,440
My God.

690
00:39:12,200 --> 00:39:15,800
Every time I think it couldn't
get more extraordinary, it surprises me.

691
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:19,520
It's impossible! I hate it!
It's evil! It's astonishing!

692
00:39:20,480 --> 00:39:22,120
I want to kiss it to death.

693
00:39:22,440 --> 00:39:23,880
COMPUTER VOICE: Attention, all crew.

694
00:39:23,960 --> 00:39:26,120
Evacuate base immediately.

695
00:39:26,200 --> 00:39:28,840
Emergency protocols have been initiated.

696
00:39:28,920 --> 00:39:31,800
This safety message
was brought to you by Vector Petroleum.

697
00:39:31,880 --> 00:39:33,760
-Fuel for our futures.
-Oh, no!

698
00:39:34,440 --> 00:39:36,400
The ghosts tampering
with the day/night settings has caused

699
00:39:36,480 --> 00:39:38,080
a computer malfunction.

700
00:39:38,160 --> 00:39:40,520
Its first priority
is to keep the reactor cool,

701
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:43,280
so it's opening the hull doors
and is flooding the base.

702
00:39:52,600 --> 00:39:54,240
LUNN: Cass says,
"Close the internal flood doors.

703
00:39:54,320 --> 00:39:56,080
"That'll contain the water
in the central corridor."”

704
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:57,920
-Where's the Tardis?
-O'DONNELL: On the other side.

705
00:39:58,000 --> 00:40:00,640
DOCTOR: We need to get there.
It's our only way out.

706
00:40:00,880 --> 00:40:03,520
OK, we've got 30 seconds
before the flood doors close.

707
00:40:05,800 --> 00:40:07,200
(PANTING)

708
00:40:08,320 --> 00:40:09,360
Come on!

709
00:40:29,320 --> 00:40:30,320
Doctor!

710
00:40:31,440 --> 00:40:32,600
(GROANS)

711
00:40:34,080 --> 00:40:35,360
(GRUNTS)

712
00:40:42,200 --> 00:40:45,520
DOCTOR: I'll get you and the others out.
Sit tight, I'll come back for you.

713
00:40:45,600 --> 00:40:47,560
CLARA: Just come over here
in the Tardis now.

714
00:40:47,640 --> 00:40:50,360
The Tardis won't go there.
It won't go near the ghosts.

715
00:40:51,920 --> 00:40:53,320
You can't just leave us!

716
00:40:55,040 --> 00:40:58,840
Listen to me. I'm going back in time
to when the spaceship landed.

717
00:40:58,920 --> 00:41:01,080
If I can understand
why this is happening,

718
00:41:01,200 --> 00:41:02,320
I can stop them killing anyone else.

719
00:41:02,400 --> 00:41:03,600
I can save you.

720
00:41:04,800 --> 00:41:05,840
You trust me, don't you, Clara?

721
00:41:16,800 --> 00:41:18,960
Wait, you're gonna go back in time?
How do you do that?

722
00:41:19,040 --> 00:41:20,120
Extremely well.

723
00:41:23,080 --> 00:41:24,440
"You're sure
they're not going to hurt us?"

724
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:26,240
They can't get out of the Faraday cage.

725
00:41:29,120 --> 00:41:30,520
(CLANKING)

726
00:41:31,040 --> 00:41:32,040
(WHOOSHING)

727
00:41:32,480 --> 00:41:34,720
DOCTOR: Back to before the flood.

728
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:44,120
"And you're sure the Doctor
won't just leave us here?”

729
00:41:44,200 --> 00:41:46,560
Guys, look. This is how we roll.

730
00:41:47,080 --> 00:41:48,320
He's gonna go away, come back,

731
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:50,000
and we'll have to listen
to how he did it.

732
00:42:01,840 --> 00:42:03,880
LUNN: Is it Moran? Or Pritchard?
Or the mole guy?

733
00:42:03,960 --> 00:42:05,480
How... How'd they get out?

734
00:42:05,560 --> 00:42:08,040
No, I don't think
it's any of them, I think it's...

735
00:42:09,040 --> 00:42:10,360
A new ghost.

736
00:42:11,360 --> 00:42:13,280
-What does that mean?
-Well, it means that

737
00:42:13,360 --> 00:42:14,560
something happened in the past,

738
00:42:14,640 --> 00:42:16,560
it means that somebody else must have...

739
00:42:20,680 --> 00:42:21,920
Oh, no!

740
00:42:23,240 --> 00:42:24,600
Oh, no, no, no, no.

741
00:42:29,960 --> 00:42:32,000
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

742
00:42:58,960 --> 00:43:01,160
Another ghost has appeared.
What does it mean?

743
00:43:01,240 --> 00:43:02,240
I have to die.

744
00:43:02,320 --> 00:43:04,080
DOCTOR: 7his is the town
before it flooded.

745
00:43:04,200 --> 00:43:06,480
I need to know how you
create these creatures.

746
00:43:06,560 --> 00:43:07,960
Nothing but words.

747
00:43:08,680 --> 00:43:10,520
He's opened the Faraday cage.
He's let the other ghosts out.

748
00:43:11,200 --> 00:43:13,880
DOCTOR: This isn't about saving me.
I am a dead man walking.

749
00:43:13,960 --> 00:43:15,240
So, who's next?

